Practical experience with the language is critical, but we do desire candidates to have some formal education in software development, typically one to two years.

00:29:02.120 --> 00:29:13.500
That training can often establish good development habits, such as setting up good unit tests, exception handling, logging practices, and commenting standards.

00:29:13.500 --> 00:29:22.440
We like when candidates can present examples of that practical experience with the language, sample code, snippets, those types of things.

