00:48:33.440 --> 00:48:37.320
So I'm going to be devil's advocate and add another response here.

00:48:37.320 --> 00:48:39.060
So for that in particular.

00:48:39.060 --> 00:48:49.120
So my advice to anyone who's a new developer looking for their first job, especially if you're someone who feels perhaps like maybe you shouldn't be in the field.

00:48:49.120 --> 00:48:50.900
Imposter syndrome is rampant.

00:48:50.900 --> 00:48:55.000
And I think many people feel like imposters, even if you've been coding since you were eight.

00:48:55.240 --> 00:49:00.780
I think what's really important is to understand the work environment you're going to be going into.

00:49:00.780 --> 00:49:04.460
First of all, you know, knowing the problem space that you'll be working in.

00:49:04.460 --> 00:49:05.660
Is that interesting to you?

00:49:05.660 --> 00:49:13.960
If you're a bit indifferent and are looking for just that first job in general, understand how you are as a person who codes.

00:49:14.180 --> 00:49:16.460
How do you learn best as a new developer?

00:49:16.460 --> 00:49:23.720
If you're a junior and this is your first time looking for a development job, it's going to be important that you have good support.

00:49:23.720 --> 00:49:26.620
So are there are there seniors that you compare with?

00:49:26.620 --> 00:49:28.180
Are there seniors who will mentor you?

00:49:28.180 --> 00:49:29.660
Is the place you're working?

00:49:29.660 --> 00:49:32.640
Do they participate with lunch talks?

00:49:32.640 --> 00:49:35.060
Do they do they care about hosting meetups?

00:49:35.060 --> 00:49:37.160
There's a few ways you can gauge this.

00:49:37.160 --> 00:49:42.800
Or, you know, you can even ask to do a coffee with the company that you're possibly going to be interviewing at.

00:49:43.960 --> 00:49:51.480
All of these things are really good ways to if you able if you can if you can do a coffee with a developer on the team, if you can go to their space when they have a meetup.

00:49:51.480 --> 00:49:55.160
All these are great ways to learn more about the team and the environment at large there.

00:49:55.160 --> 00:49:57.160
So really best advice.

00:49:57.160 --> 00:49:58.720
Be true to who you are.

00:49:58.720 --> 00:50:01.240
Know what you need in order to succeed.

00:50:01.240 --> 00:50:02.600
So set yourself up for success.

00:50:02.600 --> 00:50:05.200
Find a team that matches your style of learning.

